text:
As a pale girl in the winter, I always know with any foundation or other tinted skin product there is always a strong chance it will be too dark for me, and this unfortunately was no different. I do not want that to completely skew my review because I do think this is a good product for those who this will match and I hope to use it over the summer.
Starting with the packaging, this comes in a large box because it actually comes with a second cushion to replace when your first one is empty, the compact itself it smaller. When you open it there is a mirror, and a plastic covering to protect your cushion and store your sponge, I really like this because it keeps the cushion from drying out and rubbing on your sponge wasting product when you aren't using it.
The product itself goes on really well, it feels lighter and more silky than a liquid foundation. It provides medium coverage and doesn't feel cakey or thick. The applicator sponge has one side to apply the product and the other side has a ribbon on the back that you can use to hold it without having to touch your fingers on the front.
I ordered the color 104 which was listed as medium/light pink (it is the second to lightest color.) The stock photos online made it look like it could be a decent match for my skin. I am aware that stock photos aren't always super accurate but I will say that this turned out MUCH darker and more yellow than pink in person. The last photo in my review is the stock photo above with the actual photo of the product I received below. It doesn't go on that dark when applied to skin as you can see in the second to last photo but it is still much darker and more orange/yellow toned than I expected.
Overall I think if this matches your skin it is a great product but for anyone who is pale I can't recommend.

title_x: UM, PSA: YOU PROBABLY SHOULDN'T USE THIS ON YOUR EYEBROWS
text:
I have sparse eyebrows, always have. I usually fill them in with a pencil and then go over that with Maybelline Brow Drama. It gets my brows how I like them and it's quick to do, but I want to just be able to wake up and go, fresh faced, without worrying about putting on brows (I really like the way I look with bolder brows!)

Saw this "eyebrow tinting kit" and all the positive reviews, decided to give it a try! First concerning thing is that the instructions state THIS PRODUCT MUST NOT BE USED FOR DYEING THE EYELASHES OR EYEBROWS (probably mainly just for caution to ensure no product gets into the eyes).

Second, the instructions talked a lot about "black henna" and THIS PRODUCT MUST NOT BE USED ON SKIN AS A TEMPORARY STAIN OR TATTOO. I'm familiar with real BAQ (body art quality) henna; I've used it for reddish tints in my hair and had henna tats before. I've also read about how to be cautious about using "black henna" because henna only comes in one color - hues of red! Any other color has been altered with sketchy chemicals.

Third, the instructions has a disclaimer at the very top stating information obtained from Amazon, bloggers, or social media has not been verified by the manufacturer - basically, just because everyone else says they're using this for "eyebrow tinting", the company is telling you to follow the instructions, which specifically tells you not to use it for that, and if you choose to do so anyway, they are not legally liable.

Hmm, interesting, but, #YOLO, I want my eyebrows snatched!

Clearly, I still used this for my brows lol so I hope my face doesn't fall off. I was super excited that it actually made my brows look thicker, clearly because the skin underneath my brow hairs has been tinted (breaking rules #1 and #2). The test spot on my arm only lasted a few days and so did my brows (of course, because it only tinted the skin under my brows, and as your skin renews, the stain fades away).

Maybe this product is "good" (remember, YOU SHOULDN'T USE THIS FOR EYEBROWS!!) for people with fair colored brows and want to make them darker. It does darken hair - I tested the mixture on a grey hair of mine.

Or maybe this product should just be used for it's intended purpose: beards, mustaches, temples, sideburns, and root touch ups, but even I wouldn't use it for that since the product is "black henna", which is questionable.

Even if this product didn't have a 77.2% chance of chemically burning/peeling my face off and making me blind, it doesn't even last, so just save your coins and play it safe - if you want bolder brows, get em microbladed, use Maybelline 48hr Tattoo Studio, or just go ahead and use that trusty pencil that won't possibly leave you scarred for life.

Last note, both times I used this product, I got a headache. Idk if it's the cause of it or just a coincidence.

text:
I would like to start off by saying I absolutely adore this collection. I own it and I wear it all the time for the past few months. In fact, I loved it so much I bought it as a gift for a relative.

The wrong item was shipped to me. I was ordering the 2019 product line, titled “extra spicy” And had a little gingerbread girl and a little gingerbread boy on the lid. What was shipped to me was the 2018 product line named “gingerbread spice” with one gingerbread man on the lid.

Although the colors are lovely and many of them are very similar, what I ordered was pictured on this listing and what was shipped to me was not. So I filed a return and asked for a replacement. The second shipment came in with the same wrong item.

I called Amazon to try to see if the correct item actually exists. I do not want to order this and return it twice to get the same wrong item yet a third time.

No one could confirm if the right product is even an option at this time. It is very upsetting and I am just going to return it and find a different gift for my relative. What a shame because it is a very lovely product

text:
So I have a funny story about the foot masks! I applied the mask on Thursday night and left for a cruise on Saturday. I was ready to give the masks a good review because my feet were noticeably softer after the mask treatment. On Saturday evening (aboard the cruise ship), we sat in the hot tub for about an hour and then went back to our room. When we got there, my daughter asked what was wrong with my feet. I looked down and my feet were covered in peeling skin. I had totally forgotten about the foot mask and the fact that it specifically tells you that all the dead skin will start to peel off in about 48 hours! Well, let me tell you, that dead skin was peeling off, just like the instructions said!

So, now that I'm back from my cruise, my good review is now a great review! After I got all the peeling dead skin off, my feet are extremely soft almost all over. My heels are still a little rough but I didn't think one mask would take care of them because they were bad! I'm planning on doing a second mask tonight and I think that will take care of that little problem area.

So here's my official review:

Pros:
Very easy to apply, simply put the mask on your foot and put a sock over it to hold it on. I was still able to walk around and do what I needed to do while I had it on
Definitely works to get rid of dead skin! You should have seen all the dead skin in that trash can in our cabin! I wish I had taken a picture.

Cons:
The only con I had was the size of the mask. I wear a size 10 ladies shoe and the masks just fit me. I think anyone with a much bigger foot would have trouble getting it on and keeping it on

Overall, these masks worked great! I'm super excited to put the second application on and finish getting rid of the dead skin on my heels. I've got to get my feet sandal ready!

text:
This gel polish set from Anzuo is a decent set at a low price. The individual bottles have only a number on the top of the lid to indicate which shade is in the bottle. I saw other reviewers mention that they received a sticker sheet to use for labeling the colors; however, my box did not contain any sheet. I made a swatch chart of the colors which solves that problem, but you will need to do something in order to tell what colors are in the bottles.

I received Set #3 which has the colors black, white, dark brown, brown, tan, and red. The colors in this set are what I would consider "basics" so I don't think that I will get much wear out of these colors by themselves; however, they are nice to have on hand for nail designs. The colors do look slightly different in person (which can be expected) and I find that my red is lighter in person and the tan and brown are slightly different.

The gel itself is a bit thick compared to others that I have tried. I did have my gel at room temperature, so that was not the issue but they do recommend using warm water to get the gel to a thinner consistency. The color coverage is good, especially with two coats (which I always do.) This set does not come with its own base and top coat, so I think that longevity will depend on the quality of the base and top coat that you use. I also use a nail dehydrator before applying gel polish which helps extend the wear time as well. If you use a good base and top coat you should get 1-2 weeks of wear out of the polish.

Overall, this is a decent quality and affordable set of polishes. The colors in this particular Set #3 are basic but good for nail designs.

text:
This Hair Color Styler Wax is pretty cool stuff. I am not one to buy and use temporary hair coloring products beause most of them look really fake when applied. What caught my eye to this product is how it looked on a couple of the sample images shown with light application on this Amazon product page. The images where it shows the styler wax applied on heavy looks a bit fake and painted on. When I received this Color Styler, it came in a nice box packaging and the container is a really nice plastic twist top box. So cool! Funny that there is no English instructions on the packaging. Luckily this product is simple and self explanatory. The wax product is creamy in texture with a pearlescent sheen. Apply some onto fingers and rub against the palm of hands and onto desired hair strands. I find that when I applied it heavily into streaks, it looked really fake and Halloween-ish. The best results is a light dusted effect over dry hair and then follow with hairspray to style and hold. What is great about this product is that it washes off hands very easily and rinses off hair with one shampoo wash.
This is a very special hair wax product that is easy and fun to use. A definite keeper in my hair product arsenal and highly recomended to anyone who wants to add a touch something specail without a permanent commitment.
I received this product in excange for my honest and unbiased review. A definite 5 star product from Japan.

text: [[VIDEOID:ee381ae32ed3952623ee5f921df764d6]] La he estado utilizando ya un mes. En especial en la zona de las piernas, axilas y zona íntima. Aclaro que yo tuve tratamiento láser durante meses pero lo dejé, y medio año después compré está depiladora. Bien, pues en las piernas si he visto cambios después de la tercera semana de uso, la utilizo dos veces a la semana, los bellos casi ya no salen y los poros de la piel se han hecho chicos, ya casi ni necesito rasurarme. PERO, por otro lado, he visto pocos resultados en la zona íntima y en las axilas, posiblemente es debido a que el bello es más grueso. Actualizaré dentro de unos meses más, estoy segura que esas zonas son más complicadas por las raíces más fuertes. Me gustó la depiladora, si la recomiendo, es cómoda y práctica, no te lleva más de media hora depilarte las piernas, las axilas y la zona íntima, si se calienta déjala reposar hasta que se enfríe, esto para nivel 4 y 5. TRAE unos lentes y un rastrillo en conjunto con la depiladora, además de un instructivo. ACLARO que después de que uses la depiladora, debes de cubrir esa zona por un día, no dejes que le pegue el sol ni te pongas cremas ni nada, esto es recomendación de una dermatóloga, pueden aparecer manchas si no lo haces y puedes herir tu piel, utiliza los lentes y no uses la depiladora en zonas con cortadas o sangre, tampoco debes usar ninguna crema o ungüento cuando estés usando la depiladora. LA RECOMIENDO.
